goals.question: What is the overall trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?
goals.visualization: Line chart of the 'price' field over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the general direction of the stock market over the given time period.

goals.question: What is the distribution of daily returns for the S&P 500 index?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show how often the stock market experiences positive or negative returns on a daily basis.

goals.question: What is the average daily return for the S&P 500 index?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the median and range of daily returns, giving insight into the volatility of the stock market.

goals.question: What is the correlation between daily returns and stock prices?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show whether there is a relationship between daily returns and stock prices, which can be useful for predicting future market trends.

goals.question: What is the most common date in the dataset?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show which date appears most frequently in the dataset, which can be useful for identifying any anomalies or trends on that particular day.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['daily_return'] = pd.to_numeric(data['daily_return'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='daily_return', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['daily_return'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['daily_return'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(x=data['daily_return'].median(), color='green', label=f"Median: {data['daily_return'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of daily returns for the S&P 500 index?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    date_counts = data['date'].value_counts()
    date_counts = date_counts[date_counts > 1]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x=date_counts.index, y=date_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.axvline(x=date_counts.idxmax(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Most common date: {date_counts.idxmax().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
